CREATE TABLE claim (
    claim_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    policy_id INT NOT NULL,
    claim_date DATE NOT NULL,
    claim_amount DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
    status VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE claim (
    claim_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    policy_id INT NOT NULL,
    claim_date DATE NOT NULL,
    claim_amount DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
    status VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE policy (
    policy_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    policy_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    policy_holder_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_date DATE NOT NULL,
    end_date DATE NOT NULL
);
</t><stat>INSERT INTO policy (policy_id, policy_type, policy_holder_id, start_date, end_date) SELECT 1, 'Life Insurance', 101, '2022-01-01', '2022-12-31';</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE claim (
    claim_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    policy_id INT NOT NULL,
    claim_date DATE NOT NULL,
    claim_amount DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
    status VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE policy (
    policy_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    policy_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    policy_holder_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_date DATE NOT NULL,

);

    policy_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    holder_id UUID REFERENCES PolicyHolder(id),
    company_id UUID REFERENCES InsuranceCompany(company_id),
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE,
    premium DECIMAL

    policy_id INT,
    claim_amount DECIMAL,
    status VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE Agency (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, region STRING, agent_id INT REFERENCES Agents(id))

CREATE TABLE Policies (id INT PRIMARY KEY, policy_number STRING, policy_type STRING, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))</t><stat>insert into agency (id, name, region, agent_id) select 1, 'agency one', 'west', 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE Agency (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, region STRING, agent_id INT REFERENCES Agents(id))
